Dialogue: 0,00:00:00.000,00:00:07.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the GST scheme is a scheme that chooses in between these two...
Dialogue: 0,00:00:10.100,00:00:18.840,辉英,,0,0,0,,So we know that adding a dissipative flux proportional to delta x cubed times the third-order derivative of u
Dialogue: 0,00:00:18.840,00:00:23.100,辉英,,0,0,0,,is appropriate for smooth regions of the solution.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:23.100,00:00:30.400,辉英,,0,0,0,,And adding what we added before, a dissipation proportional to the second-order derivative,
Dialogue: 0,00:00:30.680,00:00:36.660,辉英,,0,0,0,,a much stronger dissipation because it's proportional to delta x instead of the much smaller delta x cubed,
Dialogue: 0,00:00:37.480,00:00:41.160,辉英,,0,0,0,,is appropriate around shock waves and the local extremis.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:43.060,00:00:48.420,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the GST scheme is simply a scheme that chooses in between them
Dialogue: 0,00:00:48.420,00:00:53.080,辉英,,0,0,0,,according to the same limiter we have been using to reconstruct the solution.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:53.100,00:01:07.820,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the first step is to construct a limiter phi that is equal to 0 or 1
Dialogue: 0,00:01:07.820,00:01:17.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,if 0 is non-smooth and 1 is smooth, and they can also go in between.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:17.500,00:01:21.520,辉英,,0,0,0,,So we can use the same limiter we used in our scalar conservation law.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:21.520,00:01:22.520,辉英,,0,0,0,,And second step...
Dialogue: 0,00:01:23.100,00:01:30.100,辉英,,0,0,0,,is to construct a second-order derivative...
Dialogue: 0,00:01:31.280,00:01:37.500,辉英,,0,0,0,,so second-order dissipation flux,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:38.180,00:01:46.440,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is proportional to the first-order derivative times the maximum value of the characteristic speed.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:48.020,00:01:53.080,辉英,,0,0,0,,And third step is to construct a numerical dissipation proportional...
Dialogue: 0,00:01:53.100,00:01:59.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,to the third-order derivative that is going to give us a fourth-order dissipation.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:59.020,00:02:05.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,And then combine them using the value of phi.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:05.020,00:02:12.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,In such a way that if phi is equal to 1, then we are purely using the third-order derivative.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:12.020,00:02:17.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if phi is equal to 0, we are also going to be using the first-order derivative.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:17.020,00:02:22.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,Alright, so for example, we can...
Dialogue: 0,00:02:23.100,00:02:26.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,we can multiply...
Dialogue: 0,00:02:27.020,00:02:30.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,we can have this value, the third-order derivative...
Dialogue: 0,00:02:30.020,00:02:38.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,to be also always times 1, and the second-order derivative to be times 1 minus phi.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:38.020,00:02:43.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that gives us the appropriate behavior of...
Dialogue: 0,00:02:43.020,00:02:46.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,when phi is equal to 0, we turn on the stronger dissipation.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:46.020,00:02:51.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,And when phi is equal to 1, we turn off that stronger dissipation.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:51.020,00:02:52.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,So that's...
Dialogue: 0,00:02:52.020,00:02:53.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,that's what...
Dialogue: 0,00:02:53.020,00:02:57.940,辉英,,0,0,0,,that's how the GST scheme deals with system of conservation laws.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:57.940,00:03:03.940,辉英,,0,0,0,,Achieving second-order accuracy, but still being non-oscillatory around shock waves.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:03.940,00:03:08.940,辉英,,0,0,0,,It computes the limit of the same as what we compute before.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:08.940,00:03:16.940,辉英,,0,0,0,,Based on local extremis and the ratio between slopes between different solutions.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:16.940,00:03:20.940,辉英,,0,0,0,,And construct a second-order and fourth-order dissipation.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:20.940,00:03:22.940,辉英,,0,0,0,,And perform linear conservation.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:23.020,00:03:25.940,辉英,,0,0,0,,And then we can use the combination of them,
Dialogue: 0,00:03:25.940,00:03:27.940,辉英,,0,0,0,,trimming the second-order on and off,
